  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 9 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 4 critical, 14 high, 3 medium, 18 normal. Key bases needing attention include London Luton (LTN/EGGW), Chişinău (RMO/LUKK) and Timişoara Traian Vuia (TSR/LRTR); plus 15 other bases. 3 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is mist, thunderstorm / convective risk and cold‑temperature performance penalties  — most notably around Vilnius (VNO/EYVI), Budapest Liszt Ferenc (BUD/LHBP) and M. R. Štefánik (BTS/LZIB). Network hotspots: Frankfurt-Hahn (HHN/EDFH), Memmingen Allgau (FMM/EDJA), Vilnius (VNO/EYVI), Bordeaux–Mérignac (BOD/LFBD), Budapest Liszt Ferenc (BUD/LHBP) and 4 others. Primary drivers: low cloud base, snow / blowing snow and cold‑temperature performance penalties. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Frankfurt-Hahn (HHN/EDFH), Memmingen Allgau (FMM/EDJA), Vilnius (VNO/EYVI) and 9 others.",
